Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoAddBacksideConstraint(25.10)                ecoAddBacksideConstraint(25.10)

Name
       ecoAddBacksideConstraint  -  Adds  a new backside layer constraint on a
       net

Syntax
       ecoAddBacksideConstraint

       [-help]

       -embeddedFtvCells {list of cells}

       -net <netName>

       -topPreferredLayer <top-layer-name>

       [-groupTerms {{..} {..}} | -minimumFtvs ]

       [-loc {xLoc yLoc} | { xLoc yLoc inv_xLoc inv_yLoc}  [-bufOrient  {R0  |
       R90 | R180 | R270 | MX | MX90 | MY | MY90}]]

       Adds a new backside layer constraint on a net.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each ecoAddBacksideConstraint.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man ecoAddBacksideConstraint

       -bufOrient {R0 | R90 | R180 | R270 | MX | MX90 | MY | MY90}
              Specifies the orientation for FTV instance(s)

              Valid orientation values are: R0, R90, R180, R270, MX, MX90, MY,
              MY90.

       -embeddedFtvCells {list of cells}
              Specifies the name of FTVO and FTVI cells (one each) .

       -groupTerms {{..} {..}}
              Specifies groups of terms with common FTV cell

       -loc {xLoc yLoc} | { xLoc yLoc inv_xLoc inv_yLoc}
              Specifies location(s) where FTV instance(s) will be placed.

              You can provide multiple (x y) locations as arguments. The count
              of arguments should match the number of groups  specified  using
              -groupTerms.  The  tool  will use the corresponding location for
              the corresponding group in -groupTerms.

       -minimumFtvs
              Inserts two embedded FTV cells or two FTV cells,  one  connected
              to  the  driver of the original net to go to the backside layer,
              and the other FTV drives all sinks of original nets in order  to
              go back to the frontside layer.

       -net <netName >
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  net  on which FTV cells are to be
              added.

       -topPreferredLayer <top-layer-name>
              Specifies the name of the preferred top back-side layer.

Examples
              * The following command will add FTV cell FTV_out and FTV_in  in
                the net net_A.  The FTV net from FTV_out and FTV_in will  con-
                nect through backside layer.

                ecoAddBacksideConstraint  -net net_A -embeddedFtvCells {FTV_in
                FTV_out} -topPreferredLayer B_M0

              * The following command with "-minimumFtvs" will  only  add  two
                ftvs, one connected to the driver of the original net to go to
                the  backside  layer,  and  the  other FTV drives all sinks of
                original nets.

                ecoAddBacksideConstraint -net net_A -embeddedFtvCells  {FTV_in
                FTV_out} -topPreferredLayer B_M0 -minimumFtvs

              * The  following command will place the FTVO in the location (a,
                b) FTVI in the location (c, d) when tool add two  FTV  in  the
                net_A.

                ecoAddBacksideConstraint  -net net_A -embeddedFtvCells {FTV_in
                FTV_out} -topPreferredLayer B_M0 -loc {a b c d}

